&lt;p&gt;Detailed drawings/full particulars of the proposed development showing the matters set out below must be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority, in writing, before any work is commenced. The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the details thus approved which shall be implemented in full prior to the first occupation/use of the development and retained in perpetuity (if necessary). (delete as appropriate)
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
a) Details of the proposed windows at first floor level at the front of the building in the form of 1:5 horizontal and vertical section drawings of details showing the material, profile and dimensions of the glazing bars at their junction with the glazing units; the location and depth of the glazing units; the sash boxes with weights, pulleys and cords.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;b) Details of the proposed window openings&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;at first floor level at the front of the building in the form of 1:20 horizontal and vertical section drawings showing the location of the window in the reveal, the position of the sash boxes and the material, construction and dimensions of the window arches and window cills.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;c) Detailed drawings of the proposed shopfront.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;d) Details of&amp;nbsp;all materials to be used on the external surfaces of the building. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;REASON: To ensure that the external appearance of the development is satisfactory, and preserves or enhances the character and appearance of the surrounding area. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No development shall take place until a detailed Construction Logistics Plan (CLP) covering the specific matters set out below has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
a) Hours of working&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b) Construction traffic routing&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
c) Measures to prevent dust pollution&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;d) Contact arrangements between residents and contractors&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;This should be in line with TfL CLP guidance:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://content.tfl.gov.uk/construction-logistics-plan-guidance.pdf&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;http://content.tfl.gov.uk/construction-logistics-plan-guidance.pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The development shall only be implemented in accordance with the approved details and measures relating to the specific matters set out above, which shall be maintained throughout the entire demolition/construction period.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To ensure that impacts of the construction activity on the surrounding transport network are acceptable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
